le=\"width:40em;\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5em;\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Ref\n|-\n| [[30th Golden Globe Awards|1973]]\n| ''[[The Poseidon Adventure (1972 film)|The Poseidon Adventure]]''\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Original Score|Best Original Score]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=26 | <ref>http://www.johnwilliams.org/reference/awards</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[31st Golden Globe Awards|1974]]\n| ''[[Cinderella Liberty]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ''[[Tom Sawyer (1973 film)|Tom Sawyer]]'' <small>(with [[Richard M. Sherman]] and [[Robert B. Sherman]])</small>\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[32nd Golden Globe Awards|1975]]\n| ''[[Earthquake (1974 film)|Earthquake]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[33rd Golden Globe Awards|1976]]\n| ''[[Jaws (film)|Jaws]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[35th Golden Globe Awards|1978]]\n| ''[[Star Wars (film)|Star Wars]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| ''[[Close Encounters of the Third Kind]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[36th Golden Globe Awards|1979]]\n| ''[[Superman (1978 film)|Superman]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| | [[38th Golden Globe Awards|1981]]\n| ''[[The Empire Strikes Back]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2|[[40th Golden Globe Awards|1983]]\n| ''[[E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial (soundtrack)|E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| \"If We Were In Love\" <small>(with [[Alan and Marilyn Bergman]]) from ''[[Yes, Giorgio]]''</small>\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[42nd Golden Globe Awards|1985]]\n| ''[[The River (1984 film)|The River]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[45th Golden Globe Awards|1988]]\n| ''[[Empire of the Sun (film)|Empire of the Sun]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[46th Golden Globe Awards|1989]]\n| ''[[The Accidental Tourist (film)|The Accidental Tourist]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[47th Golden Globe Awards|1990]]\n| ''[[Born on the Fourth of July (film)|Born on the Fourth of July]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[51st Golden Globe Awards|1994]]\n| ''[[Schindler's List]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[53rd Golden Globe Awards|1996]]\n| \"Moonlight\" <small>(with [[Alan and Marilyn Bergman]]) from ''[[Sabrina (1995 film)|Sabrina]]''</small>\n| Best Original Song\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[55th Golden Globe Awards|1998]]\n| ''[[Seven Years in Tibet (1997 film)|Seven Years in Tibet]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[56th Golden Globe Awards|1999]]\n| ''[[Saving Private Ryan]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[57th Golden Globe Awards|2000]]\n| ''[[Angela's Ashes (film)|Angela's Ashes]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[59th Golden Globe Awards|2002]]\n| ''[[A.I. Artificial Intelligence]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[63rd Golden Globe Awards|2006]]\n| ''[[Memoirs of a Geisha (film)|Memoirs of a Geisha]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[69th Golden Globe Awards|2012]]\n| ''[[War Horse (film)|War Horse]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[70th Golden Globe Awards|2013]]\n| ''[[Lincoln (film)|Lincoln]]\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[71st Golden Globe Awards|2014]]\n| ''[[The Book Thief (film)|The Book Thief]]\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[75th Golden Globe Awards|2018]]\n| ''[[The Post (film)|The Post]]''\n| Best Original Score\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|- style=\"border-top:2px solid gray;\"\n|}\n\n===Grammy Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Project\n! Category\n! Result\n|-\n| [[4th Grammy Awards|1962]]\n| ''Checkmate''\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Score Soundtrack for Visual Media|Best Soundtrack Album or Recording or Score from Motion Picture or Television]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[18th Grammy Awards|1975]]\n| ''[[Jaws (soundtrack)|Jaws]]''\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Score Soundtrack for Visual Media|Album of Best Original Score Written for a Motion Picture or a Television Special]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | [[20th Grammy Awards|1978]]\n| \"Main Title\" from ''Star Wars''\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Instrumental Composition|Best Instrumental Composition]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |''[[Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope (soundtrack)|Star Wars]]''\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Instrumental Performance|Best Pop Instrumental Recording]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Score Soundtrack for Visual Media|Best Original Score Written For A Motion Picture Or A Television Special]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[21st Grammy Awards|1979]]\n| \"Theme from [[Theme from Close Encounters of the Third Kind|''Close Encounters of the Third Kind'']]\"\n| Best Instrumental Composition\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| ''[[Close Encounters of the Third Kind]]''\n| Best Album of Original Score Written for a Motion Picture\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | [[22nd Grammy Awards|1980]]\n| rowspan=2 | \"Main Title Theme from ''Superman''\"\n| Best Instrumental Composition\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Pop Instrumental Performance\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ''[[Superman (1978 film)|Superman]]''\n| Best Album of Original Score Written for a Motion Picture\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | [[23rd Grammy Awards|1981]]\n| rowspan=2 | \"Yoda's Theme\"\n| Best Pop Instrumental Performance\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | Best Instrumental Composition\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| \"The Empire Strikes Back\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| \"Imperial March\" (Darth Vader's Theme)\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ''[[Star Wars Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back (soundtrack)|Star Wars Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back]]''\n| Best Album of Original Score Written for a Motion Picture\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[24th Grammy Awards|1982]]\n| ''[[Raiders of the Lost Ark (soundtrack)|Raiders of the Lost Ark]]''\n| Best Album of Original Score Written for a Motion Picture\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=5 | [[25th Grammy Awards|1983]]\n| \"Adventures on Earth\"\n| rowspan=2 | Best Instrumental Composition\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | \"Flying\" (Theme from ''E.T.'')\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Arrangement, Instrumental or A Cappella|Best Arrangement on an Instrumental Recording]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | ''[[E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial]]''\n| Best Pop Instrument Performance\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Album of Original Score Written for a Motion Picture\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[26th Grammy Awards|1984]]\n| ''[[Star Wars Episode VI: Return of the Jedi (soundtrack)|Star Wars Episode VI: Return of the Jedi]]''\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Score Soundtrack for Visual Media|Best Instrumental Composition Written for a Motion Picture or for Television]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[27th Grammy Awards|1985]]\n| ''Olympic Fanfare and Theme''\n| Best Instrumental Composition\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[28th Grammy Awards|1986]]\n| ''[[Prokofiev]]: [[Peter and the Wolf]]''\n| Best Recording for Children\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[27th Grammy Awards|1988]]\n| ''[[The Witches of Eastwick (film)|The Witches of Eastwick]]''\n| Best Instrumental Composition Written for a Motion Picture or for Television\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[28th Grammy Awards|1989]]\n| \"Olympic Spirit\"\n| Best Instrumental Composition\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ''[[Empire of the Sun (soundtrack)|Empire of the Sun]]''\n| Best Instrumental Composition Written for a Motion Picture or for Television\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[29th Grammy Awards|1990]]\n| ''[[Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade (soundtrack)|Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade]]''\n| Best Instrumental Composition Written for a Motion Picture or for Television\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[30th Grammy Awards|1991]]\n| ''Born on the Fourth of July''\n| Best Arrangement on an Instrumental Recording\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | [[31st Grammy Awards|1992]]\n| ''The Star Wars Trilogy''\n| Best Pop Instrumental Performance\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| \"Home Alone Main Title\"\n| Best 